name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.connect.timeout
description:
Expert: The maximum amount of time (in milli seconds) reduce
  task spends in trying to connect to a remote node for getting map output.

name: dfs.namenode.list.cache.pools.num.responses
description:
This value controls the number of cache pools that the NameNode will
    send over the wire in response to a listPools RPC.

name: dfs.client.key.provider.cache.expiry
description: DFS client security key cache expiration in milliseconds.

name: ipc.server.max.connections
description:
The maximum number of concurrent connections a server is allowed
    to accept. If this limit is exceeded, incoming connections will first fill
    the listen queue and then may go to an OS-specific listen overflow queue.
    The client may fail or timeout, but the server can avoid running out of file
    descriptors using this feature. 0 means no limit.

name: dfs.namenode.accesstime.precision
description:
The access time for HDFS file is precise upto this value. 
               The default value is 1 hour. Setting a value of 0 disables
               access times for HDFS.

name: fs.s3a.paging.maximum
description:
How many keys to request from S3 when doing
     directory listings at a time.

name: dfs.namenode.delegation.token.max-lifetime
description:
The maximum lifetime in milliseconds for which a delegation 
      token is valid.
